<emphasis box="[940,992,1081,1105]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1017,1079,1082,1106]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It can easily be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[395,543,1117,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[395,543,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Japanagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the numerous spines of different sizes present on the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
